Matchup numero deux: St. Louis Rams at Atlanta Falcons

                For Saturday this is the exciteing one, two very evenly matched teams on both sides of the ball. Both teams are gonna have to go into this with the same strategy to knock off the other. Atlanta will have to contain marc bulger and st. louis will have to stop michael vick. Then it's all unpredictability from there for the day. If Mike V is stopped you have a dynamic duo of warrick dunn and t.j. duckett in the backfield with superb blocking skills by the fullback justin griffith to deal with which AINT no easy task. On the other side in St. louies hands is marshall faulk and stephen jackson with a offensive line in front of them that holds such a name as orlando pace one of the best linemen the game has ever seen. What the game will boil down to is defense, defense wins championships and that is what will win this game. If atlantas defense comes to play i see them comeing out on top.

Prediction: Atlanta 13 over St. Louis 10

Matchup numero uh 3: Minnesota Vikings at Philadelphia Eagles

           The key thing to look at here is the Vikings post season turn around last week against the at the time HOTT green bay packers. If philadelphia wasn't watching that game then they should be smacked. Last week the Vikings broke their curse of failing to meet expectations when it comes to being a post season contender by spanking the packers. Now we'll have to look to see how they do against a very rested TOless eagles. Prediction: Eagles 24 Vikings 17

Final Matchup of the weekend Indianapolis Colts at New England Patriots

By the looks of things this game may turn into a battle of offenses, which is almost a term unheard of when you speak of the patriots but because of injuries this year the pats D hasn't been up to par as it has been through out the previous years and we all know the colts lack in defense but that unit has surprised most this year being small and fast does pay off in some situations and that is the number one advantage the colts D has. This one will all come down to offense and more offense a brady vs. manning and dillon vs. james day see who can rack up the most yards and touchdowns. In my opinion the pats wont be able to stop manning this year.

Prediction: Colts 34 Patriots 31
